<subSubSection pageId="139" pageNumber="141" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="139.[979,1275,423,447]" box="[979,1275,423,447]" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">
<heading box="[979,1275,423,447]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="139" pageNumber="141" reason="4">
<taxonomicName authority="Ewing, 1917" authorityName="Ewing" authorityYear="1917" box="[979,1275,423,447]" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Atropacarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="139" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[979,1126,423,447]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">Atropacarus</emphasis>
Ewing, 1917
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="139.[826,1429,486,1197]" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">
Body integumental surface covered with concavities. Posterior furrows of prodorsum present, lamellar setae minute (length ratio of lamellar setae/prodorsum &lt;0.2). Ventral region; genital setae in a row or nearly so, distance between setae 
<emphasis box="[1353,1366,627,650]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">g</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[1367,1376,636,653]" fontSize="7" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">6</subScript>
and 
<emphasis box="[826,839,662,685]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">g</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[839,848,671,688]" fontSize="7" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">5</subScript>
longer than that between 
<emphasis box="[1164,1177,662,685]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">g</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[1177,1186,671,688]" fontSize="7" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">5</subScript>
and 
<emphasis box="[1249,1262,662,685]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">g</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[1262,1271,671,688]" fontSize="7" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">4</subScript>
; setae 
<emphasis box="[1355,1380,662,686]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">ad</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[1380,1389,671,688]" fontSize="7" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">1</subScript>
always close to paraxial margin, in a row with anal setae; setae 
<emphasis box="[966,991,732,756]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">ad</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[991,1000,741,758]" fontSize="7" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">2</subScript>
remote from the paraxial margin or close to it. Legs; setae 
<emphasis box="[1086,1107,767,790]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">v’</emphasis>
on femora I minute, length ratio 
<emphasis box="[887,900,803,826]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">v</emphasis>
&quot;/ 
<emphasis box="[926,947,802,825]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">v’</emphasis>
&lt;2.2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="139" pageNumber="141" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="139.[826,1429,486,1197]" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">
Distribution — Semicosmopolitan subgenus – 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1923" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1923" box="[1002,1309,900,924]" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Hoplophorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="139" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1002,1152,900,924]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">Hoplophorella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese A." box="[1159,1309,900,924]" pageId="139" pageNumber="141" pagination="237 - 262" refId="ref67369" refString="Berlese A. 1923 - Centuria sesta di Acari nuovi - Redia, 15, 237 - 262." type="journal article" year="1923">Berlese, 1923</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="139.[826,1429,486,1197]" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">
15 pairs of notogastral setae, as a rule only two pairs of lyrifissures, 
<emphasis box="[1073,1092,984,1007]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">ia</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1156,1184,984,1007]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">im</emphasis>
present. Ventral region; nine pairs of genital setae arranged in a single row and five pairs of anal and adanal setae present; setae 
<emphasis box="[891,916,1089,1113]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">ad</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[916,925,1098,1115]" fontSize="7" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">2</subScript>
remote from the paraxial margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="139.[826,1429,486,1197]" pageId="139" pageNumber="141">Distribution — Pantropical, uncommon in northern hemisphere.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
